<div id="p370" class="blockpost rowodd">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#5&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=370#p370">2008-08-20 16:05:22</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=89618">The 8472</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Azureus Developer</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: bep 27: private torrents</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Putting it inside the info-dict alters the torrent hash and thus enforces the private-flag as disabling it by editing the .torrent file would change the hash. And since the private flag only works if everyone obeys it it shouldn't be possible to remove it easily.<br /><br />It also allows you to create 2 distinct swarms (1 for the public tracker, 1 for the private one) with otherwise identical properties.</p>
					<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by The 8472 (2008-08-20 16:06:34)</em></p>
				</div>
				<div class="postsignature"><hr />Az dev</div>
			</div>
