<div id="p439" class="blockpost rowodd">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#15&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=439#p439">2008-09-03 11:55:30</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=30435">bram</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Administrator</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: bep 27: private torrents</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Good grief. I'm not exactly arguing with you, I'm just saying that if you actually believe what you're saying you should call for optional keys within the infodict which give the tracker urls. Please either acknowledge that as a logical extension of the argument for a private flag in the infodict, or give some reason why the logic which applies to the private flag shouldn't apply to the tracker urls, or drop the argument about the private flag.<br /><br />Putting the tracker urls within the infodict would have a clear immediate benefit in at least one case you mention - when the client switches between trackers, if all trackers were listed in the info dict there would be no reason to drop all connections when doing the tracker switchover.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
