<div id="p447" class="blockpost rowodd">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#19&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=447#p447">2008-09-04 14:53:57</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=89601">dave</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Editor</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: bep 27: private torrents</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>If we want to make it possible to modify metadata like the &quot;private&quot; flag, then one way to do this is to optionally put the URL of the .torrent file inside the info dict.&nbsp; When a BitTorrent client is passed a .torrent the first time, the client redownloads the .torrent from the URL in the info dict.&nbsp; We can then move everything else outside the infodict except the piece hashes.&nbsp; <br /><br />This allows the private tracker site to change metainfo at will including announce-lists and the private flag.&nbsp; <br /><br />However, I won't go forward with formally proposing such an extension until a private tracker operator asks for it.&nbsp; I would prefer to make the semantics of private=1 match the semantics of existing implementations.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
			<div class="postfootleft"><p>Offline</p></div>
			<div class="postfootright"><div>&nbsp;</div></div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div id="p449" class="blockpost roweven">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#20&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=449#p449">2008-09-04 16:40:46</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
